{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775860458095,"sessionID":"ses_286782798ffenf5WpAnJjFdiZH","part":{"id":"prt_d79882234001WIt65F8sR5FpsC","messageID":"msg_d798810cd001OVmDeBiKoW472D","sessionID":"ses_286782798ffenf5WpAnJjFdiZH","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-66831d07e34c4784a7e066444e65f19b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-016/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-016/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # PicoD 文件管理 API Design\n2: \n3: ## AR-016 — PicoD 文件管理 API\n4: \n5: **Module**: `pkg/picod`\n6: **Language**: Go\n7: **Purpose**: Extend PicoD file management capabilities with Kubernetes client-go integration, enabling centralized management of PicoD instances and their workspaces through custom Kubernetes resources (AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter).\n8: \n9: ## Overview\n10: \n11: PicoD file management API provides secure file operations within isolated workspace jails. AR-016 enhances this by integrating with Kubernetes through the generated client-go library, allowing PicoD instances to be managed as Kubernetes resources while maintaining existing HTTP-based file management APIs. This integration enables lifecycle management, health monitoring, and workspace orchestration at the Kubernetes level.\n12: \n13: ### Key Requirements\n14: \n15: - Maintain existing HTTP-based file management APIs (upload, list, download)\n16: - Integrate with Kubernetes client-go for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources\n17: - Support workspace provisioning and management through Kubernetes custom resources\n18: - Enable health status reporting to Kubernetes via status subresource\n19: - Provide watch/informer capabilities for real-time resource updates\n20: - Maintain workspace jail security and path sanitization\n21: - Support graceful shutdown and cleanup of workspaces\n22: - Enable multi-tenant isolation through namespace separation\n23: \n24: ## Architecture\n25: \n26: ### Package Structure\n27: \n28: ```\n29: pkg/picod/\n30: ├── auth.go                    # JWT authentication (existing)\n31: ├── execute.go                 # Command execution (existing)\n32: ├── files.go                   # File management handlers (existing)\n33: ├── server.go                  # HTTP server (existing)\n34: ├── handlers.go                # HTTP handlers (existing)\n35: ├── middleware.go              # Middleware (existing)\n36: ├── errors.go                  # Error handling (existing)\n37: ├── config.go                  # Configuration (existing)\n38: ├── constants.go               # Constants (existing)\n39: ├── k8s_integration.go         # NEW: Kubernetes client integration\n40: ├── workspace_manager.go       # NEW: Workspace lifecycle management\n41: ├── status_reporter.go         # NEW: Status reporting to Kubernetes\n42: └── informer.go                # NEW: Resource informers and event handlers\n43: \n44: changes/AR-016/\n45: ├── design.md                  # This document\n46: ├── spec.md                    # API specification\n47: ├── CHANGE.md                  # Change log\n48: └── IMPLEMENTATION_SUMMARY.md  # Implementation summary\n49: ```\n50: \n51: ### Component Interactions\n52: \n53: ```\n54: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n55: │                        Kubernetes Cluster                               │\n56: │                                                                          │\n57: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n58: │  │                   API Server                                     │   │\n59: │  │  - AgentRuntime CRD                                              │   │\n60: │  │  - CodeInterpreter CRD                                           │   │\n61: │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n62: │                                │                                        │\n63: │                                │ REST API                               │\n64: │                                │                                        │\n65: │  ┌─────────────────────────────▼─────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n66: │  │                 PicoD Controller (Optional)                       │  │\n67: │  │  - Creates/updates AgentRuntime resources                         │  │\n68: │  │  - Manages PicoD instance lifecycle                               │  │\n69: │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n70: │                                                                          │\n71: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n72:                                   │\n73:                                   │ HTTP API (JWT Auth)\n74:                                   │\n75: ┌─────────────────────────────────▼─────────────────────────────────────────┐\n76: │                          PicoD Instance                                  │\n77: │                                                                           │\n78: │  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐     │\n79: │  │              HTTP Server (Gin)                                  │     │\n80: │  │  - /api/execute                                                │     │\n81: │  │  - /api/files (upload, list, download)                          │     │\n82: │  │  - /health                                                      │     │\n83: │  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘     │\n84: │                                  │                                        │\n85: │  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐     │\n86: │  │         Kubernetes Client Integration                           │     │\n87: │  │  - Clientset for Runtime API                                    │     │\n88: │  │  - Informers for AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter                   │     │\n89: │  │  - Status reporting (UpdateStatus)                              │     │\n90: │  │  - Watch events (Add, Update, Delete)                           │     │\n91: │  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘     │\n92: │                                  │                                        │\n93: │  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐     │\n94: │  │         Workspace Manager                                       │     │\n95: │  │  - Workspace provisioning                                       │     │\n96: │  │  - Path sanitization and jail enforcement                       │     │\n97: │  │  - File operations (upload, list, download)                     │     │\n98: │  │  - Cleanup and garbage collection                               │     │\n99: │  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘     │\n100: │                                  │                                        │\n101: │  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐     │\n102: │  │         Status Reporter                                         │     │\n103: │  │  - Health status aggregation                                     │     │\n104: │  │  - File system statistics                                       │     │\n105: │  │  - Resource usage metrics                                       │     │\n106: │  │  - Error conditions and events                                  │     │\n107: │  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘     │\n108: │                                                                           │\n109: └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n110:                                   │\n111:                                   │\n112: ┌─────────────────────────────────▼─────────────────────────────────────────┐\n113: │                    Shared Workspace Volume                                │\n114: │                                                                           │\n115: │  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐     │\n116: │  │         Workspace Directory                                     │     │\n117: │  │  - User files                                                   │     │\n118: │  │  - Code artifacts                                               │     │\n119: │  │  - Execution outputs                                            │     │\n120: │  │  - Temporary files                                              │     │\n121: │  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘     │\n122: │                                                                           │\n123: └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n124: ```\n125: \n126: ### Request Flow with Kubernetes Integration\n127: \n128: ```\n129: 1. Kubernetes Resource Creation\n130:    ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n131:    │ User/Controller creates AgentRuntime CRD instance           │\n132:    │                                                              │\n133:    │ apiVersion: runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1           │\n134:    │ kind: AgentRuntime                                           │\n135:    │ metadata:                                                    │\n136:    │   name: my-agent                                             │\n137:    │   namespace: default                                         │\n138:    │ spec:                                                        │\n139:    │   image: volcano-sh/agentcube-agent:latest                   │\n140:    │   workspaceSize: \"1Gi\"                                       │\n141:    └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n142:                            │\n143:                            ▼\n144:    ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n145:    │ Kubernetes API Server validates and stores the resource     │\n146:    └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n147:                            │\n148:                            ▼\n149:    ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n150:    │ PicoD Pod scheduled with AgentRuntime reference             │\n151:    │ Environment variables injected:                             │\n152:    │ - AGENTRUNTIME_NAME, AGENTRUNTIME_NAMESPACE                 │\n153:    └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n154: \n155: 2. PicoD Initialization\n156:    ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n157:    │ PicoD starts and initializes Kubernetes client              │\n158:    │                                                              │\n159:    │ - Loads in-cluster configuration                            │\n160:    │ - Creates clientset for Runtime API                         │\n161:    │ - Starts informers for AgentRuntime resources               │\n162:    │ - Retrieves corresponding AgentRuntime resource            │\n163:    │ - Provisions workspace directory                            │\n164:    │ - Starts status reporter goroutine                          │\n165:    └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n166: \n167: 3. File Management Operations (HTTP API)\n168:    POST /api/files\n169:    ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n170:    │ HTTP Request (JWT authenticated)                             │\n171:    │ - Upload file to workspace                                   │\n172:    │                                                              │\n173:    │ PicoD processes:                                             │\n174:    │ - Validates JWT token                                        │\n175:    │ - Sanitizes file path                                        │\n176:    │ - Writes file to workspace                                   │\n177:    │ - Updates workspace statistics                              │\n178:    │ - Triggers status update (async)                             │\n179:    └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n180: \n181: 4. Status Reporting (Async)\n182:    ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n183:    │ Status Reporter periodically updates Kubernetes             │\n184:    │                                                              │\n185:    │ - Collects file system stats                                 │\n186:    │ - Aggregates health status                                   │\n187:    │ - Calls client.UpdateStatus()                                │\n188:    │                                                              │\n189:    │ Status subresource updated:                                  │\n190:    │ status:                                                      │\n191:    │   phase: \"Running\"                                           │\n192:    │   workspace:                                                 │\n193:    │     fileCount: 42                                            │\n194:    │     totalSize: \"1024MiB\"                                     │\n195:    │     lastModified: \"2024-01-01T00:00:00Z\"                     │\n196:    └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n197: \n198: 5. Watch Events (Informers)\n199:    ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n200:    │ Informer receives events from Kubernetes                    │\n201:    │                                                              │\n202:    │ - AgentRuntime deleted → Cleanup workspace, shutdown        │\n203:    │ - AgentRuntime updated → Apply configuration changes        │\n204:    │ - ConfigMap changed → Reload configuration                  │\n205:    └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n206: ```\n207: \n208: ## Data Structures\n209: \n210: ### Kubernetes Client Integration\n211: \n212: **File**: `pkg/picod/k8s_integration.go`\n213: \n214: ```go\n215: // K8sClient manages Kubernetes client operations\n216: type K8sClient struct {\n217: \tclientset       *agentcubeclientset.Clientset\n218: \tagentRuntimeClient runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeInterface\n219: \tcodeInterpreterClient runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreterInterface\n220: \tnamespace       string\n221: \tagentRuntimeName string\n222: \tinformerFactory informers.SharedInformerFactory\n223: \tstopCh          chan struct{}\n224: }\n225: \n226: // K8sConfig holds Kubernetes client configuration\n227: type K8sConfig struct {\n228: \tInCluster      bool\n229: \tKubeconfigPath string\n230: \tNamespace      string\n231: \tAgentRuntimeName string\n232: \tAgentRuntimeNamespace string\n233: }\n234: \n235: // NewK8sClient creates a new Kubernetes client\n236: func NewK8sClient(config K8sConfig) (*K8sClient, error) {\n237: \tvar kubeConfig *rest.Config\n238: \tvar err error\n239: \n240: \tif config.InCluster {\n241: \t\tkubeConfig, err = rest.InClusterConfig()\n242: \t} else if config.KubeconfigPath != \"\" {\n243: \t\tkubeConfig, err = clientcmd.BuildConfigFromFlags(\"\", config.KubeconfigPath)\n244: \t} else {\n245: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"either in-cluster or kubeconfig path must be specified\")\n246: \t}\n247: \n248: \tif err != nil {\n249: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to build kubeconfig: %w\", err)\n250: \t}\n251: \n252: \tclientset, err := agentcubeclientset.NewForConfig(kubeConfig)\n253: \tif err != nil {\n254: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to create clientset: %w\", err)\n255: \t}\n256: \n257: \tnamespace := config.Namespace\n258: \tif namespace == \"\" {\n259: \t\tif config.InCluster {\n260: \t\t\tnamespaceBytes, err := os.ReadFile(\"/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/namespace\")\n261: \t\t\tif err != nil {\n262: \t\t\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to read namespace from service account: %w\", err)\n263: \t\t\t}\n264: \t\t\tnamespace = string(namespaceBytes)\n265: \t\t} else {\n266: \t\t\tnamespace = \"default\"\n267: \t\t}\n268: \t}\n269: \n270: \tinformerFactory := informers.NewSharedInformerFactory(clientset, time.Minute*10)\n271: \n272: \treturn &K8sClient{\n273: \t\tclientset:            clientset,\n274: \t\tagentRuntimeClient:   clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(namespace),\n275: \t\tcodeInterpreterClient: clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().CodeInterpreters(namespace),\n276: \t\tnamespace:            namespace,\n277: \t\tagentRuntimeName:     config.AgentRuntimeName,\n278: \t\tstopCh:               make(chan struct{}),\n279: \t\tinformerFactory:      informerFactory,\n280: \t}, nil\n281: }\n282: \n283: // GetAgentRuntime retrieves the AgentRuntime resource\n284: func (k *K8sClient) GetAgentRuntime(ctx context.Context, name string) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error) {\n285: \treturn k.agentRuntimeClient.Get(ctx, name, metav1.GetOptions{})\n286: }\n287: \n288: // UpdateAgentRuntimeStatus updates the status subresource\n289: func (k *K8sClient) UpdateAgentRuntimeStatus(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error) {\n290: \treturn k.agentRuntimeClient.UpdateStatus(ctx, agentRuntime, metav1.UpdateOptions{})\n291: }\n292: \n293: // GetCodeInterpreter retrieves the CodeInterpreter resource\n294: func (k *K8sClient) GetCodeInterpreter(ctx context.Context, name string) (*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, error) {\n295: \treturn k.codeInterpreterClient.Get(ctx, name, metav1.GetOptions{})\n296: }\n297: \n298: // UpdateCodeInterpreterStatus updates the status subresource\n299: func (k *K8sClient) UpdateCodeInterpreterStatus(ctx context.Context, codeInterpreter *runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter) (*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, error) {\n300: \treturn k.codeInterpreterClient.UpdateStatus(ctx, codeInterpreter, metav1.UpdateOptions{})\n301: }\n302: \n303: // StartInformers starts the informers and waits for cache sync\n304: func (k *K8sClient) StartInformers() {\n305: \tk.informerFactory.Start(k.stopCh)\n306: }\n307: \n308: // WaitForCacheSync waits for informer caches to sync\n309: func (k *K8sClient) WaitForCacheSync() map[reflect.Type]bool {\n310: \treturn k.informerFactory.WaitForCacheSync(k.stopCh)\n311: }\n312: \n313: // Stop stops the informers\n314: func (k *K8sClient) Stop() {\n315: \tclose(k.stopCh)\n316: }\n317: ```\n318: \n319: ### Workspace Manager\n320: \n321: **File**: `pkg/picod/workspace_manager.go`\n322: \n323: ```go\n324: // WorkspaceManager manages workspace lifecycle\n325: type WorkspaceManager struct {\n326: \tworkspaceDir     string\n327: \tk8sClient       *K8sClient\n328: \tmetrics         WorkspaceMetrics\n329: \tmetricsMutex    sync.RWMutex\n330: }\n331: \n332: // WorkspaceMetrics holds workspace statistics\n333: type WorkspaceMetrics struct {\n334: \tFileCount       int64     `json:\"file_count\"`\n335: \tTotalSize       int64     `json:\"total_size\"`\n336: \tLastModified    time.Time `json:\"last_modified\"`\n337: \tDirectoryCount  int64     `json:\"directory_count\"`\n338: }\n339: \n340: // NewWorkspaceManager creates a new workspace manager\n341: func NewWorkspaceManager(workspaceDir string, k8sClient *K8sClient) (*WorkspaceManager, error) {\n342: \tif err := os.MkdirAll(workspaceDir, DefaultDirMode); err != nil {\n343: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to create workspace directory: %w\", err)\n344: \t}\n345: \n346: \treturn &WorkspaceManager{\n347: \t\tworkspaceDir: workspaceDir,\n348: \t\tk8sClient:   k8sClient,\n349: \t\tmetrics:     WorkspaceMetrics{},\n350: \t}, nil\n351: }\n352: \n353: // ProvisionWorkspace provisions a new workspace directory\n354: func (wm *WorkspaceManager) ProvisionWorkspace() error {\n355: \tif err := os.MkdirAll(wm.workspaceDir, DefaultDirMode); err != nil {\n356: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"failed to provision workspace: %w\", err)\n357: \t}\n358: \treturn nil\n359: }\n360: \n361: // CleanupWorkspace cleans up the workspace directory\n362: func (wm *WorkspaceManager) CleanupWorkspace() error {\n363: \tif err := os.RemoveAll(wm.workspaceDir); err != nil {\n364: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"failed to cleanup workspace: %w\", err)\n365: \t}\n366: \treturn nil\n367: }\n368: \n369: // UpdateMetrics updates workspace metrics\n370: func (wm *WorkspaceManager) UpdateMetrics() error {\n371: \tmetrics, err := wm.calculateMetrics()\n372: \tif err != nil {\n373: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"failed to calculate workspace metrics: %w\", err)\n374: \t}\n375: \n376: \twm.metricsMutex.Lock()\n377: \twm.metrics = metrics\n378: \twm.metricsMutex.Unlock()\n379: \n380: \treturn nil\n381: }\n382: \n383: // calculateMetrics calculates workspace statistics\n384: func (wm *WorkspaceManager) calculateMetrics() (WorkspaceMetrics, error) {\n385: \tvar metrics WorkspaceMetrics\n386: \tvar totalSize int64\n387: \tvar fileCount, dirCount int64\n388: \tvar lastModified time.Time\n389: \n390: \terr := filepath.Walk(wm.workspaceDir, func(path string, info os.FileInfo, err error) error {\n391: \t\tif err != nil {\n392: \t\t\treturn err\n393: \t\t}\n394: \n395: \t\tif info.IsDir() {\n396: \t\t\tdirCount++\n397: \t\t} else {\n398: \t\t\tfileCount++\n399: \t\t\ttotalSize += info.Size()\n400: \t\t\tif info.ModTime().After(lastModified) {\n401: \t\t\t\tlastModified = info.ModTime()\n402: \t\t\t}\n403: \t\t}\n404: \n405: \t\treturn nil\n406: \t})\n407: \n408: \tif err != nil {\n409: \t\treturn WorkspaceMetrics{}, err\n410: \t}\n411: \n412: \tmetrics.FileCount = fileCount\n413: \tmetrics.TotalSize = totalSize\n414: \tmetrics.LastModified = lastModified\n415: \tmetrics.DirectoryCount = dirCount\n416: \n417: \treturn metrics, nil\n418: }\n419: \n420: // GetMetrics returns current workspace metrics\n421: func (wm *WorkspaceManager) GetMetrics() WorkspaceMetrics {\n422: \twm.metricsMutex.RLock()\n423: \tdefer wm.metricsMutex.RUnlock()\n424: \treturn wm.metrics\n425: }\n426: ```\n427: \n428: ### Status Reporter\n429: \n430: **File**: `pkg/picod/status_reporter.go`\n431: \n432: ```go\n433: // StatusReporter reports status to Kubernetes\n434: type StatusReporter struct {\n435: \tk8sClient       *K8sClient\n436: \tworkspaceManager *WorkspaceManager\n437: \tagentRuntimeName string\n438: \tinterval        time.Duration\n439: \tstopCh          chan struct{}\n440: }\n441: \n442: // NewStatusReporter creates a new status reporter\n443: func NewStatusReporter(k8sClient *K8sClient, workspaceManager *WorkspaceManager, agentRuntimeName string, interval time.Duration) *StatusReporter {\n444: \treturn &StatusReporter{\n445: \t\tk8sClient:        k8sClient,\n446: \t\tworkspaceManager: workspaceManager,\n447: \t\tagentRuntimeName: agentRuntimeName,\n448: \t\tinterval:        interval,\n449: \t\tstopCh:          make(chan struct{}),\n450: \t}\n451: }\n452: \n453: // Start starts the status reporter\n454: func (sr *StatusReporter) Start() {\n455: \tticker := time.NewTicker(sr.interval)\n456: \tdefer ticker.Stop()\n457: \n458: \tfor {\n459: \t\tselect {\n460: \t\tcase <-ticker.C:\n461: \t\t\tif err := sr.reportStatus(); err != nil {\n462: \t\t\t\tklog.Errorf(\"Failed to report status: %v\", err)\n463: \t\t\t}\n464: \t\tcase <-sr.stopCh:\n465: \t\t\treturn\n466: \t\t}\n467: \t}\n468: }\n469: \n470: // Stop stops the status reporter\n471: func (sr *StatusReporter) Stop() {\n472: \tclose(sr.stopCh)\n473: }\n474: \n475: // reportStatus reports the current status to Kubernetes\n476: func (sr *StatusReporter) reportStatus() error {\n477: \tctx, cancel := context.WithTimeout(context.Background(), 10*time.Second)\n478: \tdefer cancel()\n479: \n480: \tagentRuntime, err := sr.k8sClient.GetAgentRuntime(ctx, sr.agentRuntimeName)\n481: \tif err != nil {\n482: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"failed to get AgentRuntime: %w\", err)\n483: \t}\n484: \n485: \tif err := sr.workspaceManager.UpdateMetrics(); err != nil {\n486: \t\tklog.Warningf(\"Failed to update workspace metrics: %v\", err)\n487: \t}\n488: \n489: \tmetrics := sr.workspaceManager.GetMetrics()\n490: \n491: \tagentRuntime.Status.Phase = \"Running\"\n492: \tagentRuntime.Status.Workspace.FileCount = metrics.FileCount\n493: \tagentRuntime.Status.Workspace.TotalSize = metrics.TotalSize\n494: \tagentRuntime.Status.Workspace.LastModified = metav1.NewTime(metrics.LastModified)\n495: \tagentRuntime.Status.Workspace.DirectoryCount = metrics.DirectoryCount\n496: \n497: \t_, err = sr.k8sClient.UpdateAgentRuntimeStatus(ctx, agentRuntime)\n498: \tif err != nil {\n499: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"failed to update AgentRuntime status: %w\", err)\n500: \t}\n501: \n502: \tklog.V(2).Infof(\"Successfully reported status for AgentRuntime %s\", sr.agentRuntimeName)\n503: \treturn nil\n504: }\n505: ```\n506: \n507: ### Informer Event Handlers\n508: \n509: **File**: `pkg/picod/informer.go`\n510: \n511: ```go\n512: // InformerManager manages informer event handlers\n513: type InformerManager struct {\n514: \tk8sClient         *K8sClient\n515: \tserver            *Server\n516: \tworkspaceManager  *WorkspaceManager\n517: }\n518: \n519: // NewInformerManager creates a new informer manager\n520: func NewInformerManager(k8sClient *K8sClient, server *Server, workspaceManager *WorkspaceManager) *InformerManager {\n521: \treturn &InformerManager{\n522: \t\tk8sClient:        k8sClient,\n523: \t\tserver:           server,\n524: \t\tworkspaceManager: workspaceManager,\n525: \t}\n526: }\n527: \n528: // SetupAgentRuntimeInformer sets up AgentRuntime informer\n529: func (im *InformerManager) SetupAgentRuntimeInformer() {\n530: \tinformer := im.k8sClient.informerFactory.Runtime().V1alpha1().AgentRuntimes().Informer()\n531: \n532: \tinformer.AddEventHandler(cache.ResourceEventHandlerFuncs{\n533: \t\tAddFunc: func(obj interface{}) {\n534: \t\t\tagentRuntime := obj.(*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime)\n535: \t\t\tklog.Infof(\"AgentRuntime %s added\", agentRuntime.Name)\n536: \t\t},\n537: \t\tUpdateFunc: func(oldObj, newObj interface{}) {\n538: \t\t\toldAgentRuntime := oldObj.(*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime)\n539: \t\t\tnewAgentRuntime := newObj.(*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime)\n540: \n541: \t\t\tif !reflect.DeepEqual(oldAgentRuntime.Spec, newAgentRuntime.Spec) {\n542: \t\t\t\tklog.Infof(\"AgentRuntime %s spec updated\", newAgentRuntime.Name)\n543: \t\t\t\tim.handleSpecUpdate(newAgentRuntime)\n544: \t\t\t}\n545: \t\t},\n546: \t\tDeleteFunc: func(obj interface{}) {\n547: \t\t\tagentRuntime := obj.(*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime)\n548: \t\t\tklog.Infof(\"AgentRuntime %s deleted, initiating shutdown\", agentRuntime.Name)\n549: \t\t\tim.handleAgentRuntimeDeletion(agentRuntime)\n550: \t\t},\n551: \t})\n552: }\n553: \n554: // SetupCodeInterpreterInformer sets up CodeInterpreter informer\n555: func (im *InformerManager) SetupCodeInterpreterInformer() {\n556: \tinformer := im.k8sClient.informerFactory.Runtime().V1alpha1().CodeInterpreters().Informer()\n557: \n558: \tinformer.AddEventHandler(cache.ResourceEventHandlerFuncs{\n559: \t\tAddFunc: func(obj interface{}) {\n560: \t\t\tcodeInterpreter := obj.(*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter)\n561: \t\t\tklog.Infof(\"CodeInterpreter %s added\", codeInterpreter.Name)\n562: \t\t},\n563: \t\tUpdateFunc: func(oldObj, newObj interface{}) {\n564: \t\t\toldCodeInterpreter := oldObj.(*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter)\n565: \t\t\tnewCodeInterpreter := newObj.(*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter)\n566: \n567: \t\t\tif !reflect.DeepEqual(oldCodeInterpreter.Spec, newCodeInterpreter.Spec) {\n568: \t\t\t\tklog.Infof(\"CodeInterpreter %s spec updated\", newCodeInterpreter.Name)\n569: \t\t\t\tim.handleCodeInterpreterUpdate(newCodeInterpreter)\n570: \t\t\t}\n571: \t\t},\n572: \t\tDeleteFunc: func(obj interface{}) {\n573: \t\t\tcodeInterpreter := obj.(*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter)\n574: \t\t\tklog.Infof(\"CodeInterpreter %s deleted\", codeInterpreter.Name)\n575: \t\t},\n576: \t})\n577: }\n578: \n579: // handleSpecUpdate handles AgentRuntime spec updates\n580: func (im *InformerManager) handleSpecUpdate(agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime) {\n581: \tif agentRuntime.Spec.WorkspaceSize != nil {\n582: \t\tklog.Infof(\"Workspace size updated to %s\", *agentRuntime.Spec.WorkspaceSize)\n583: \t}\n584: \n585: \tif agentRuntime.Spec.TerminationGracePeriodSeconds != nil {\n586: \t\tklog.Infof(\"Termination grace period updated to %d\", *agentRuntime.Spec.TerminationGracePeriodSeconds)\n587: \t}\n588: }\n589: \n590: // handleAgentRuntimeDeletion handles AgentRuntime deletion\n591: func (im *InformerManager) handleAgentRuntimeDeletion(agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime) {\n592: \tif agentRuntime.Name == im.k8sClient.agentRuntimeName {\n593: \t\tklog.Info(\"This PicoD instance's AgentRuntime was deleted, initiating graceful shutdown\")\n594: \n595: \t\tctx, cancel := context.WithTimeout(context.Background(), 30*time.Second)\n596: \t\tdefer cancel()\n597: \n598: \t\tif err := im.workspaceManager.CleanupWorkspace(); err != nil {\n599: \t\t\tklog.Errorf(\"Failed to cleanup workspace: %v\", err)\n600: \t\t}\n601: \n602: \t\tif err := im.server.Shutdown(ctx); err != nil {\n603: \t\t\tklog.Errorf(\"Failed to shutdown server: %v\", err)\n604: \t\t}\n605: \n606: \t\tos.Exit(0)\n607: \t}\n608: }\n609: \n610: // handleCodeInterpreterUpdate handles CodeInterpreter updates\n611: func (im *InformerManager) handleCodeInterpreterUpdate(codeInterpreter *runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter) {\n612: \tif codeInterpreter.Spec.RuntimeName == im.k8sClient.agentRuntimeName {\n613: \t\tklog.Infof(\"CodeInterpreter %s for this runtime updated\", codeInterpreter.Name)\n614: \t}\n615: }\n616: ```\n617: \n618: ### Server Integration\n619: \n620: **Modified File**: `pkg/picod/server.go`\n621: \n622: ```go\n623: type Server struct {\n624: \tengine           *gin.Engine\n625: \tconfig           Config\n626: \tauthManager      *AuthManager\n627: \tstartTime        time.Time\n628: \tworkspaceDir     string\n629: \thttpServer       *http.Server\n630: \tk8sClient        *K8sClient\n631: \tworkspaceManager *WorkspaceManager\n632: \tstatusReporter   *StatusReporter\n633: \tinformerManager  *InformerManager\n634: }\n635: \n636: func NewServer(config Config) (*Server, error) {\n637: \tworkspace := config.Workspace\n638: \tif workspace == \"\" {\n639: \t\tcwd, err := os.Getwd()\n640: \t\tif err != nil {\n641: \t\t\treturn nil, NewError(ErrServerInternal, \"failed to get current working directory\", err.Error(), err)\n642: \t\t}\n643: \t\tworkspace = cwd\n644: \t}\n645: \n646: \tabsWorkspace, err := filepath.Abs(workspace)\n647: \tif err != nil {\n648: \t\treturn nil, NewError(ErrServerInternal, \"failed to resolve workspace path\", err.Error(), err)\n649: \t}\n650: \n651: \tif err := os.MkdirAll(absWorkspace, DefaultDirMode); err != nil {\n652: \t\treturn nil, NewError(ErrServerInternal, \"failed to create workspace directory\", err.Error(), err)\n653: \t}\n654: \n655: \tauthManager, err := NewAuthManager()\n656: \tif err != nil {\n657: \t\treturn nil, err\n658: \t}\n659: \n660: \tgin.SetMode(gin.ReleaseMode)\n661: \tengine := gin.New()\n662: \tengine.Use(gin.Recovery())\n663: \tengine.Use(gin.Logger())\n664: \n665: \tserver := &Server{\n666: \t\tengine:       engine,\n667: \t\tconfig:       config,\n668: \t\tauthManager:  authManager,\n669: \t\tstartTime:    time.Now(),\n670: \t\tworkspaceDir: absWorkspace,\n671: \t}\n672: \n673: \tserver.registerRoutes()\n674: \n675: \tif config.K8sConfig != nil {\n676: \t\tk8sClient, err := NewK8sClient(*config.K8sConfig)\n677: \t\tif err != nil {\n678: \t\t\tklog.Warningf(\"Failed to create Kubernetes client: %v\", err)\n679: \t\t} else {\n680: \t\t\tserver.k8sClient = k8sClient\n681: \n682: \t\t\tworkspaceManager, err := NewWorkspaceManager(absWorkspace, k8sClient)\n683: \t\t\tif err != nil {\n684: \t\t\t\tklog.Warningf(\"Failed to create workspace manager: %v\", err)\n685: \t\t\t} else {\n686: \t\t\t\tserver.workspaceManager = workspaceManager\n687: \n688: \t\t\t\tif k8sClient.agentRuntimeName != \"\" {\n689: \t\t\t\t\tstatusReporter := NewStatusReporter(k8sClient, workspaceManager, k8sClient.agentRuntimeName, time.Minute)\n690: \t\t\t\t\tserver.statusReporter = statusReporter\n691: \t\t\t\t\tgo statusReporter.Start()\n692: \n693: \t\t\t\t\tinformerManager := NewInformerManager(k8sClient, server, workspaceManager)\n694: \t\t\t\t\tserver.informerManager = informerManager\n695: \t\t\t\t\tinformerManager.SetupAgentRuntimeInformer()\n696: \t\t\t\t\tinformerManager.SetupCodeInterpreterInformer()\n697: \n698: \t\t\t\t\tk8sClient.StartInformers()\n699: \t\t\t\t\tsynced := k8sClient.WaitForCacheSync()\n700: \t\t\t\t\tklog.Infof(\"Informer cache sync: %v\", synced)\n701: \t\t\t\t}\n702: \t\t\t}\n703: \t\t}\n704: \t}\n705: \n706: \treturn server, nil\n707: }\n708: \n709: func (s *Server) Shutdown(ctx context.Context) error {\n710: \tklog.Info(\"Shutting down server...\")\n711: \n712: \tif s.statusReporter != nil {\n713: \t\ts.statusReporter.Stop()\n714: \t}\n715: \n716: \tif s.k8sClient != nil {\n717: \t\ts.k8sClient.Stop()\n718: \t}\n719: \n720: \tif err := s.httpServer.Shutdown(ctx); err != nil {\n721: \t\treturn err\n722: \t}\n723: \n724: \tklog.Info(\"Server shutdown complete\")\n725: \treturn nil\n726: }\n727: ```\n728: \n729: ### Configuration Extension\n730: \n731: **Modified File**: `pkg/picod/config.go`\n732: \n733: ```go\n734: type Config struct {\n735: \tPort      int          `json:\"port\"`\n736: \tWorkspace string       `json:\"workspace\"`\n737: \tK8sConfig *K8sConfig   `json:\"k8s_config,omitempty\"`\n738: }\n739: \n740: type K8sConfig struct {\n741: \tInCluster           bool   `json:\"in_cluster\"`\n742: \tKubeconfigPath      string `json:\"kubeconfig_path\"`\n743: \tNamespace           string `json:\"namespace\"`\n744: \tAgentRuntimeName    string `json:\"agent_runtime_name\"`\n745: \tAgentRuntimeNamespace string `json:\"agent_runtime_namespace\"`\n746: }\n747: ```\n748: \n749: ## API Contracts\n750: \n751: ### Existing HTTP APIs (Unchanged)\n752: \n753: All existing HTTP APIs remain unchanged:\n754: \n755: - **POST /api/execute**: Execute commands in workspace\n756: - **POST /api/files**: Upload files to workspace (multipart or JSON Base64)\n757: - **GET /api/files**: List files in workspace directory\n758: - **GET /api/files/*path**: Download files from workspace\n759: - **GET /health**: Health check (no authentication)\n760: \n761: ### Kubernetes Resource Status\n762: \n763: The AgentRuntime status subresource is updated with workspace information:\n764: \n765: ```yaml\n766: apiVersion: runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1\n767: kind: AgentRuntime\n768: metadata:\n769:   name: my-agent\n770:   namespace: default\n771: spec:\n772:   image: volcano-sh/agentcube-agent:latest\n773:   workspaceSize: \"1Gi\"\n774: status:\n775:   phase: \"Running\"\n776:   workspace:\n777:     fileCount: 42\n778:     totalSize: 1073741824\n779:     lastModified: \"2024-01-01T00:00:00Z\"\n780:     directoryCount: 8\n781:   conditions:\n782:     - type: \"Ready\"\n783:       status: \"True\"\n784:       lastTransitionTime: \"2024-01-01T00:00:00Z\"\n785:       reason: \"WorkspaceInitialized\"\n786:       message: \"Workspace initialized and ready\"\n787: ```\n788: \n789: ## Error Handling\n790: \n791: ### Kubernetes Integration Errors\n792: \n793: **File**: `pkg/picod/errors.go` (Extended)\n794: \n795: ```go\n796: const (\n797: \t// Kubernetes errors\n798: \tErrK8sConnectionFailed    = \"K8sConnectionFailed\"\n799: \tErrK8sResourceNotFound    = \"K8sResourceNotFound\"\n800: \tErrK8sUpdateFailed        = \"K8sUpdateFailed\"\n801: \tErrK8sInformerFailed      = \"K8sInformerFailed\"\n802: \tErrK8sConfigInvalid       = \"K8sConfigInvalid\"\n803: \n804: \t// Workspace errors\n805: \tErrWorkspaceProvisionFailed = \"WorkspaceProvisionFailed\"\n806: \tErrWorkspaceCleanupFailed   = \"WorkspaceCleanupFailed\"\n807: \tErrWorkspaceMetricsFailed   = \"WorkspaceMetricsFailed\"\n808: )\n809: \n810: var statusCodeMap = map[string]int{\n811: \t// Existing error codes...\n812: \tErrK8sConnectionFailed:      http.StatusServiceUnavailable,\n813: \tErrK8sResourceNotFound:      http.StatusNotFound,\n814: \tErrK8sUpdateFailed:          http.StatusInternalServerError,\n815: \tErrK8sInformerFailed:        http.StatusInternalServerError,\n816: \tErrK8sConfigInvalid:         http.StatusBadRequest,\n817: \tErrWorkspaceProvisionFailed: http.StatusInternalServerError,\n818: \tErrWorkspaceCleanupFailed:   http.StatusInternalServerError,\n819: \tErrWorkspaceMetricsFailed:   http.StatusInternalServerError,\n820: }\n821: ```\n822: \n823: ### Error Recovery Strategy\n824: \n825: 1. **Kubernetes Connection Failures**:\n826:    - Log error and continue in degraded mode (HTTP APIs still work)\n827:    - Retry connection with exponential backoff\n828:    - Mark Kubernetes integration as unavailable in health check\n829: \n830: 2. **Resource Update Failures**:\n831:    - Retry with backoff (up to 5 attempts)\n832:    - Log error and continue (non-critical)\n833:    - Queue status update for next reporting cycle\n834: \n835: 3. **Informer Failures**:\n836:    - Restart informer with backoff\n837:    - Log error and continue\n838:    - Health check indicates informer status\n839: \n840: 4. **Workspace Failures**:\n841:    - Log error and fail the operation\n842:    - Return HTTP 500 to client\n843:    - Update Kubernetes status with error condition\n844: \n845: ## Testing Strategy\n846: \n847: ### Unit Tests\n848: \n849: **File**: `pkg/picod/k8s_integration_test.go`\n850: \n851: ```go\n852: func TestK8sClientCreation(t *testing.T) {\n853: \ttests := []struct {\n854: \t\tname        string\n855: \t\tconfig      K8sConfig\n856: \t\tsetupEnv    func()\n857: \t\tcleanupEnv  func()\n858: \t\twantErr     bool\n859: \t}{\n860: \t\t{\n861: \t\t\tname: \"in-cluster config\",\n862: \t\t\tconfig: K8sConfig{\n863: \t\t\t\tInCluster: true,\n864: \t\t\t},\n865: \t\t\twantErr: false,\n866: \t\t},\n867: \t\t{\n868: \t\t\tname: \"kubeconfig path\",\n869: \t\t\tconfig: K8sConfig{\n870: \t\t\t\tKubeconfigPath: \"/tmp/test-kubeconfig\",\n871: \t\t\t},\n872: \t\t\twantErr: false,\n873: \t\t},\n874: \t\t{\n875: \t\t\tname:   \"no config\",\n876: \t\t\tconfig: K8sConfig{},\n877: \t\t\twantErr: true,\n878: \t\t},\n879: \t}\n880: \n881: \tfor _, tt := range tests {\n882: \t\tt.Run(tt.name, func(t *testing.T) {\n883: \t\t\tif tt.setupEnv != nil {\n884: \t\t\t\ttt.setupEnv()\n885: \t\t\t}\n886: \t\t\tif tt.cleanupEnv != nil {\n887: \t\t\t\tdefer tt.cleanupEnv()\n888: \t\t\t}\n889: \n890: \t\t\tclient, err := NewK8sClient(tt.config)\n891: \t\t\tif (err != nil) != tt.wantErr {\n892: \t\t\t\tt.Errorf(\"NewK8sClient() error = %v, wantErr %v\", err, tt.wantErr)\n893: \t\t\t}\n894: \n895: \t\t\tif !tt.wantErr && client != nil {\n896: \t\t\t\tif client.namespace == \"\" {\n897: \t\t\t\t\tt.Error(\"Expected non-empty namespace\")\n898: \t\t\t\t}\n899: \t\t\t}\n900: \t\t})\n901: \t}\n902: }\n903: \n904: func TestK8sClientOperations(t *testing.T) {\n905: \tif testing.Short() {\n906: \t\tt.Skip(\"Skipping integration test in short mode\")\n907: \t}\n908: \n909: \tclient := setupTestK8sClient(t)\n910: \tdefer cleanupTestK8sClient(t, client)\n911: \n912: \tctx := context.Background()\n913: \n914: \tt.Run(\"get non-existent resource\", func(t *testing.T) {\n915: \t\t_, err := client.GetAgentRuntime(ctx, \"non-existent\")\n916: \t\tif err == nil {\n917: \t\t\tt.Error(\"Expected error for non-existent resource\")\n918: \t\t}\n919: \t})\n920: \n921: \tt.Run(\"update status\", func(t *testing.T) {\n922: \t\tagentRuntime := &runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{\n923: \t\t\tObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n924: \t\t\t\tName: \"test-agent\",\n925: \t\t\t},\n926: \t\t\tStatus: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeStatus{\n927: \t\t\t\tPhase: \"Running\",\n928: \t\t\t},\n929: \t\t}\n930: \n931: \t\t_, err := client.UpdateAgentRuntimeStatus(ctx, agentRuntime)\n932: \t\tif err == nil {\n933: \t\t\tt.Error(\"Expected error for non-existent resource\")\n934: \t\t}\n935: \t})\n936: }\n937: ```\n938: \n939: **File**: `pkg/picod/workspace_manager_test.go`\n940: \n941: ```go\n942: func TestWorkspaceManager(t *testing.T) {\n943: \tworkspace := t.TempDir()\n944: \tk8sClient := &K8sClient{}\n945: \n946: \tmanager, err := NewWorkspaceManager(workspace, k8sClient)\n947: \trequire.NoError(t, err)\n948: \n949: \tt.Run(\"provision workspace\", func(t *testing.T) {\n950: \t\terr := manager.ProvisionWorkspace()\n951: \t\trequire.NoError(t, err)\n952: \n953: \t\tif _, err := os.Stat(workspace); os.IsNotExist(err) {\n954: \t\t\tt.Error(\"Workspace directory should exist\")\n955: \t\t}\n956: \t})\n957: \n958: \tt.Run(\"update metrics on empty workspace\", func(t *testing.T) {\n959: \t\terr := manager.UpdateMetrics()\n960: \t\trequire.NoError(t, err)\n961: \n962: \t\tmetrics := manager.GetMetrics()\n963: \t\tif metrics.FileCount != 0 {\n964: \t\t\tt.Errorf(\"Expected 0 files, got %d\", metrics.FileCount)\n965: \t\t}\n966: \t})\n967: \n968: \tt.Run(\"update metrics with files\", func(t *testing.T) {\n969: \t\ttestFile := filepath.Join(workspace, \"test.txt\")\n970: \t\terr := os.WriteFile(testFile, []byte(\"test content\"), 0644)\n971: \t\trequire.NoError(t, err)\n972: \n973: \t\terr = manager.UpdateMetrics()\n974: \t\trequire.NoError(t, err)\n975: \n976: \t\tmetrics := manager.GetMetrics()\n977: \t\tif metrics.FileCount != 1 {\n978: \t\t\tt.Errorf(\"Expected 1 file, got %d\", metrics.FileCount)\n979: \t\t}\n980: \t\tif metrics.TotalSize != len(\"test content\") {\n981: \t\t\tt.Errorf(\"Expected size %d, got %d\", len(\"test content\"), metrics.TotalSize)\n982: \t\t}\n983: \t})\n984: \n985: \tt.Run(\"cleanup workspace\", func(t *testing.T) {\n986: \t\terr := manager.CleanupWorkspace()\n987: \t\trequire.NoError(t, err)\n988: \n989: \t\tif _, err := os.Stat(workspace); !os.IsNotExist(err) {\n990: \t\t\tt.Error(\"Workspace directory should not exist after cleanup\")\n991: \t\t}\n992: \t})\n993: }\n994: ```\n995: \n996: **File**: `pkg/picod/status_reporter_test.go`\n997: \n998: ```go\n999: func TestStatusReporter(t *testing.T) {\n1000: \tk8sClient := setupTestK8sClient(t)\n1001: \tdefer cleanupTestK8sClient(t, k8sClient)\n1002: \n1003: \tworkspace := t.TempDir()\n1004: \tworkspaceManager, err := NewWorkspaceManager(workspace, k8sClient)\n1005: \trequire.NoError(t, err)\n1006: \n1007: \treporter := NewStatusReporter(k8sClient, workspaceManager, \"test-agent\", time.Second)\n1008: \n1009: \tt.Run(\"report status\", func(t *testing.T) {\n1010: \t\terr := reporter.reportStatus()\n1011: \t\trequire.NoError(t, err)\n1012: \t})\n1013: }\n1014: \n1015: func TestStatusReporterStart(t *testing.T) {\n1016: \tk8sClient := setupTestK8sClient(t)\n1017: \tdefer cleanupTestK8sClient(t, k8sClient)\n1018: \n1019: \tworkspace := t.TempDir()\n1020: \tworkspaceManager, err := NewWorkspaceManager(workspace, k8sClient)\n1021: \trequire.NoError(t, err)\n1022: \n1023: \treporter := NewStatusReporter(k8sClient, workspaceManager, \"test-agent\", 100*time.Millisecond)\n1024: \n1025: \tgo reporter.Start()\n1026: \n1027: \ttime.Sleep(300 * time.Millisecond)\n1028: \n1029: \treporter.Stop()\n1030: }\n1031: ```\n1032: \n1033: **File**: `pkg/picod/informer_test.go`\n1034: \n1035: ```go\n1036: func TestInformerManager(t *testing.T) {\n1037: \tk8sClient := setupTestK8sClient(t)\n1038: \tdefer cleanupTestK8sClient(t, k8sClient)\n1039: \n1040: \tworkspace := t.TempDir()\n1041: \tworkspaceManager, err := NewWorkspaceManager(workspace, k8sClient)\n1042: \trequire.NoError(t, err)\n1043: \n1044: \tserver := &Server{}\n1045: \tinformerManager := NewInformerManager(k8sClient, server, workspaceManager)\n1046: \n1047: \tt.Run(\"setup agent runtime informer\", func(t *testing.T) {\n1048: \t\tinformerManager.SetupAgentRuntimeInformer()\n1049: \t})\n1050: \n1051: \tt.Run(\"setup code interpreter informer\", func(t *testing.T) {\n1052: \t\tinformerManager.SetupCodeInterpreterInformer()\n1053: \t})\n1054: }\n1055: ```\n1056: \n1057: ### Integration Tests\n1058: \n1059: **File**: `pkg/picod/k8s_integration_test.go`\n1060: \n1061: ```go\n1062: func TestK8sIntegrationFullWorkflow(t *testing.T) {\n1063: \tif testing.Short() {\n1064: \t\tt.Skip(\"Skipping integration test in short mode\")\n1065: \t}\n1066: \n1067: \tctx := context.Background()\n1068: \n1069: \tworkspace := t.TempDir()\n1070: \n1071: \tk8sConfig := K8sConfig{\n1072: \t\tInCluster:           false,\n1073: \t\tKubeconfigPath:      os.Getenv(\"KUBECONFIG\"),\n1074: \t\tNamespace:           \"default\",\n1075: \t\tAgentRuntimeName:    \"test-agent-runtime\",\n1076: \t}\n1077: \n1078: \tk8sClient, err := NewK8sClient(k8sConfig)\n1079: \trequire.NoError(t, err)\n1080: \tdefer k8sClient.Stop()\n1081: \n1082: \tworkspaceManager, err := NewWorkspaceManager(workspace, k8sClient)\n1083: \trequire.NoError(t, err)\n1084: \n1085: \tstatusReporter := NewStatusReporter(k8sClient, workspaceManager, \"test-agent-runtime\", time.Second)\n1086: \tgo statusReporter.Start()\n1087: \tdefer statusReporter.Stop()\n1088: \n1089: \tinformerManager := NewInformerManager(k8sClient, &Server{}, workspaceManager)\n1090: \tinformerManager.SetupAgentRuntimeInformer()\n1091: \n1092: \tk8sClient.StartInformers()\n1093: \tsynced := k8sClient.WaitForCacheSync()\n1094: \trequire.True(t, synced.All())\n1095: \n1096: \tt.Run(\"workspace provisioning and metrics\", func(t *testing.T) {\n1097: \t\ttestFile := filepath.Join(workspace, \"test.txt\")\n1098: \t\terr := os.WriteFile(testFile, []byte(\"test content\"), 0644)\n1099: \t\trequire.NoError(t, err)\n1100: \n1101: \t\terr = workspaceManager.UpdateMetrics()\n1102: \t\trequire.NoError(t, err)\n1103: \n1104: \t\tmetrics := workspaceManager.GetMetrics()\n1105: \t\trequire.Equal(t, int64(1), metrics.FileCount)\n1106: \t})\n1107: }\n1108: ```\n1109: \n1110: ## Dependencies\n1111: \n1112: ### Go Module Dependencies (Extended)\n1113: \n1114: ```go\n1115: require (\n1116:     github.com/gin-gonic/gin v1.10.0\n1117:     github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5 v5.2.0\n1118:     k8s.io/klog/v2 v2.130.1\n1119:     github.com/stretchr/testify v1.9.0\n1120:     k8s.io/client-go v0.30.3\n1121:     k8s.io/apimachinery v0.30.3\n1122:     k8s.io/api v0.30.3\n1123:     github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go v0.0.1\n1124: )\n1125: ```\n1126: \n1127: ### External Dependencies\n1128: \n1129: - **Gin Framework**: HTTP routing and middleware (existing)\n1130: - **JWT Library**: RSA-based JWT token validation (existing)\n1131: - **klog**: Structured logging (existing)\n1132: - **Kubernetes client-go**: Kubernetes API client (new)\n1133: - **AgentCube client-go**: Custom resource client (new)\n1134: - **Go Standard Library**: exec, os, filepath, time, context, crypto/rsa (existing)\n1135: \n1136: ## Security Considerations\n1137: \n1138: ### Authentication and Authorization\n1139: \n1140: - All HTTP APIs continue to require JWT authentication (unchanged)\n1141: - Kubernetes client uses in-cluster config or provided kubeconfig\n1142: - RBAC permissions required for PicoD service account:\n1143:   ```yaml\n1144:   apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n1145:   kind: Role\n1146:   metadata:\n1147:     name: picod-role\n1148:   rules:\n1149:   - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n1150:     resources: [\"agentruntimes\", \"codeinterpreters\"]\n1151:     verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"update\", \"updatestatus\"]\n1152:   ```\n1153: \n1154: ### Workspace Security\n1155: \n1156: - Path sanitization unchanged (existing security measures maintained)\n1157: - Workspace jail enforcement prevents directory traversal\n1158: - Symlink resolution and validation (existing)\n1159: - All file operations restricted to workspace directory\n1160: \n1161: ### Kubernetes Integration Security\n1162: \n1163: - PicoD only updates status subresource, cannot modify spec\n1164: - Limited RBAC permissions to prevent unauthorized modifications\n1165: - Service account tokens used for authentication\n1166: - No privileged access to cluster resources\n1167: \n1168: ### Error Message Security\n1169: \n1170: - Error messages do not expose sensitive Kubernetes information\n1171: - File paths in error messages remain relative to workspace\n1172: - Kubernetes errors logged but not exposed to HTTP clients\n1173: \n1174: ## Integration Points\n1175: \n1176: ### With AgentCube Platform\n1177: \n1178: PicoD integrates with AgentCube components through Kubernetes resources:\n1179: \n1180: - **Sandbox Orchestrator**: Creates AgentRuntime resources referencing PicoD instances\n1181: - **WorkloadManager**: Monitors AgentRuntime status for health and readiness\n1182: - **Session Store**: Queries AgentRuntime resources for workspace information\n1183: - **Controller**: Manages AgentRuntime lifecycle and configuration\n1184: \n1185: ### Deployment Integration\n1186: \n1187: ```yaml\n1188: apiVersion: v1\n1189: kind: Pod\n1190: metadata:\n1191:   name: picod-pod\n1192:   namespace: default\n1193: spec:\n1194:   serviceAccountName: picod\n1195:   containers:\n1196:   - name: picod\n1197:     image: volcano-sh/picod:latest\n1198:     env:\n1199:     - name: PICOD_K8S_IN_CLUSTER\n1200:       value: \"true\"\n1201:     - name: PICOD_K8S_AGENT_RUNTIME_NAME\n1202:       valueFrom:\n1203:         fieldRef:\n1204:           fieldPath: metadata.annotations['agentcube.volcano.sh/agent-runtime']\n1205:     - name: PICOD_K8S_NAMESPACE\n1206:       valueFrom:\n1207:         fieldRef:\n1208:           fieldPath: metadata.namespace\n1209:     - name: PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY\n1210:       valueFrom:\n1211:         secretKeyRef:\n1212:           name: picod-auth-keys\n1213:           key: public-key\n1214:     volumeMounts:\n1215:     - name: workspace\n1216:       mountPath: /workspace\n1217:   volumes:\n1218:   - name: workspace\n1219:     emptyDir:\n1220:       sizeLimit: 1Gi\n1221: ```\n1222: \n1223: ### Service Account\n1224: \n1225: ```yaml\n1226: apiVersion: v1\n1227: kind: ServiceAccount\n1228: metadata:\n1229:   name: picod\n1230: ---\n1231: apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n1232: kind: Role\n1233: metadata:\n1234:   name: picod-role\n1235: rules:\n1236: - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n1237:   resources: [\"agentruntimes\"]\n1238:   verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"update\", \"updatestatus\"]\n1239: - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n1240:   resources: [\"codeinterpreters\"]\n1241:   verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"]\n1242: ---\n1243: apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n1244: kind: RoleBinding\n1245: metadata:\n1246:   name: picod-role-binding\n1247: subjects:\n1248: - kind: ServiceAccount\n1249:   name: picod\n1250: roleRef:\n1251:   kind: Role\n1252:   name: picod-role\n1253:   apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io\n1254: ```\n1255: \n1256: ## Configuration\n1257: \n1258: ### CLI Flags (Extended)\n1259: \n1260: | Flag                | Type   | Default | Description |\n1261: |---------------------|--------|---------|-------------|\n1262: | `-port`             | int    | 8080    | Port for the PicoD server to listen on |\n1263: | `-workspace`        | string | \"\"      | Root directory for file operations |\n1264: | `-k8s-in-cluster`   | bool   | false   | Use in-cluster Kubernetes config |\n1265: | `-k8s-kubeconfig`   | string | \"\"      | Path to kubeconfig file |\n1266: | `-k8s-namespace`    | string | \"\"      | Kubernetes namespace |\n1267: | `-k8s-agent-runtime`| string | \"\"      | AgentRuntime resource name |\n1268: \n1269: ### Environment Variables (Extended)\n1270: \n1271: | Name                          | Required | Description |\n1272: |-------------------------------|----------|-------------|\n1273: | `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY`       | Yes      | PEM-encoded RSA public key for JWT validation |\n1274: | `PICOD_K8S_IN_CLUSTER`        | No       | Set to \"true\" to use in-cluster config |\n1275: | `PICOD_K8S_KUBECONFIG`        | No       | Path to kubeconfig file |\n1276: | `PICOD_K8S_NAMESPACE`         | No       | Kubernetes namespace |\n1277: | `PICOD_K8S_AGENT_RUNTIME_NAME`| No       | AgentRuntime resource name |\n1278: \n1279: ### Configuration Example\n1280: \n1281: ```yaml\n1282: apiVersion: v1\n1283: kind: ConfigMap\n1284: metadata:\n1285:   name: picod-config\n1286: data:\n1287:   PORT: \"8080\"\n1288:   WORKSPACE: \"/workspace\"\n1289:   PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY: |\n1290:     -----BEGIN PUBLIC KEY-----\n1291:     MIIBIjANBgkqhkiG9w0BAQEFAAOCAQ8AMIIBCgKCAQEA...\n1292:     -----END PUBLIC KEY-----\n1293:   PICOD_K8S_IN_CLUSTER: \"true\"\n1294:   PICOD_K8S_AGENT_RUNTIME_NAME: \"my-agent-runtime\"\n1295: ```\n1296: \n1297: ## Documentation\n1298: \n1299: ### API Documentation\n1300: \n1301: All existing HTTP APIs remain unchanged and documented in AR-015.\n1302: \n1303: ### Kubernetes Integration Documentation\n1304: \n1305: **Setup PicoD with Kubernetes Integration**:\n1306: ```bash\n1307: # Start PicoD with in-cluster config\n1308: ./picod -port 8080 -workspace /workspace -k8s-in-cluster -k8s-agent-runtime my-agent\n1309: \n1310: # Start PicoD with kubeconfig\n1311: ./picod -port 8080 -workspace /workspace -k8s-kubeconfig ~/.kube/config -k8s-agent-runtime my-agent -k8s-namespace default\n1312: ```\n1313: \n1314: **Monitoring AgentRuntime Status**:\n1315: ```bash\n1316: # Get AgentRuntime status\n1317: kubectl get agentruntime my-agent -o yaml\n1318: \n1319: # Watch AgentRuntime status updates\n1320: kubectl get agentruntime my-agent -w\n1321: \n1322: # Get workspace statistics from status\n1323: kubectl get agentruntime my-agent -o jsonpath='{.status.workspace}'\n1324: ```\n1325: \n1326: ### Usage Examples\n1327: \n1328: **Deploy PicoD with Kubernetes Integration**:\n1329: ```yaml\n1330: apiVersion: apps/v1\n1331: kind: Deployment\n1332: metadata:\n1333:   name: picod\n1334: spec:\n1335:   replicas: 1\n1336:   selector:\n1337:     matchLabels:\n1338:       app: picod\n1339:   template:\n1340:     metadata:\n1341:       labels:\n1342:         app: picod\n1343:       annotations:\n1344:         agentcube.volcano.sh/agent-runtime: my-agent\n1345:     spec:\n1346:       serviceAccountName: picod\n1347:       containers:\n1348:       - name: picod\n1349:         image: volcano-sh/picod:latest\n1350:         args:\n1351:         - -port=8080\n1352:         - -workspace=/workspace\n1353:         - -k8s-in-cluster\n1354:         env:\n1355:         - name: PICOD_K8S_AGENT_RUNTIME_NAME\n1356:           valueFrom:\n1357:             fieldRef:\n1358:               fieldPath: metadata.annotations['agentcube.volcano.sh/agent-runtime']\n1359:         - name: PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY\n1360:           valueFrom:\n1361:             secretKeyRef:\n1362:               name: picod-auth-keys\n1363:               key: public-key\n1364:         volumeMounts:\n1365:         - name: workspace\n1366:           mountPath: /workspace\n1367:       volumes:\n1368:       - name: workspace\n1369:         emptyDir:\n1370:           sizeLimit: 1Gi\n1371: ```\n1372: \n1373: ## Success Criteria\n1374: \n1375: - [ ] HTTP file management APIs continue to work unchanged\n1376: - [ ] Kubernetes client successfully connects and authenticates\n1377: - [ ] AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources can be retrieved\n1378: - [ ] Status subresource updates succeed with workspace metrics\n1379: - [ ] Informers receive and handle resource events correctly\n1380: - [ ] Workspace manager provisions and cleans up workspaces\n1381: - [ ] Status reporter periodically updates Kubernetes resources\n1382: - [ ] Path sanitization and security remain effective\n1383: - [ ] Error handling covers Kubernetes integration failures\n1384: - [ ] Unit tests cover all new code paths\n1385: - [ ] Integration tests validate Kubernetes workflows\n1386: - [ ] RBAC permissions are correctly configured\n1387: - [ ] Graceful shutdown handles Kubernetes resource deletion\n1388: - [ ] Health check reflects Kubernetes integration status\n1389: - [ ] Documentation covers setup and usage patterns\n1390: \n1391: ## Migration Notes\n1392: \n1393: ### Backward Compatibility\n1394: \n1395: - All existing HTTP APIs remain unchanged\n1396: - Kubernetes integration is optional (disabled by default)\n1397: - PicoD can run without Kubernetes client (degraded mode)\n1398: - No breaking changes to existing deployments\n1399: \n1400: ### Upgrading from AR-015\n1401: \n1402: To enable Kubernetes integration:\n1403: \n1404: 1. Update PicoD deployment to include service account\n\n(Output capped at 50 KB. Showing lines 1-1404. Use offset=1405 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# PicoD 文件管理 API Design\n\n## AR-016 — PicoD 文件管理 API\n\n**Module**: `pkg/picod`\n**Language**: Go\n**Purpose**: Extend PicoD file management capabilities with Kubernetes client-go integration, enabling centralized management of PicoD instances and their workspaces through custom Kubernetes resources (AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter).\n\n## Overview\n\nPicoD file management API provides secure file operations within isolated workspace jails. AR-016 enhances this by integrating with Kubernetes through the generated client-go library, allowing PicoD instances to be managed as Kubernetes resources while maintaining existing HTTP-based file management APIs. This integration enables lifecycle management, health monitoring, and workspace orchestration at the Kubernetes level.\n\n### Key Requirements\n\n- Maintain existing HTTP-based file management APIs (upload, list, download)\n- Integrate with Kubernetes client-go for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources\n- Support workspace provisioning and management through Kubernetes custom resources\n- Enable health status reporting to Kubernetes via status subresource\n- Provide watch/informer capabilities for real-time resource updates\n- Maintain workspace jail security and path sanitization","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-016/design.md","time":{"s