{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775860458097,"sessionID":"ses_286782798ffenf5WpAnJjFdiZH","part":{"id":"prt_d79881b2e001B3LyuxKCb1lD4w","messageID":"msg_d798810cd001OVmDeBiKoW472D","sessionID":"ses_286782798ffenf5WpAnJjFdiZH","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-df5e9e11800e48c88db42f5f84571ed3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-016/IMPLEMENTATION_SUMMARY.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-016/IMPLEMENTATION_SUMMARY.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-016 Implementation Summary\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: Successfully implemented the PicoD file management API with Kubernetes integration, enabling centralized management of PicoD instances and their workspaces through Kubernetes custom resources (AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter).\n5: \n6: ## Implementation Details\n7: \n8: ### New Files Created\n9: \n10: #### 1. `pkg/picod/k8s_integration.go`\n11: - **K8sClient**: Manages Kubernetes client operations\n12:   - Dynamic client for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRDs\n13:   - Support for in-cluster and kubeconfig-based authentication\n14:   - Informer factory setup for watch/informer capabilities\n15:   - Methods for CRUD operations on AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources\n16:   - Status update support via UpdateStatus\n17:   - Watch capabilities for real-time resource updates\n18: \n19: #### 2. `pkg/picod/workspace_manager.go`\n20: - **WorkspaceManager**: Manages workspace lifecycle\n21:   - Provision and cleanup workspace directories\n22:   - Track workspace metrics (file count, total size, directory count, last modified)\n23:   - Path resolution with security enforcement (workspace jail)\n24:   - File existence checks, size retrieval, mode retrieval\n25:   - Directory operations (create, delete, list)\n26:   - Recursive operations support\n27: \n28: #### 3. `pkg/picod/status_reporter.go`\n29: - **StatusReporter**: Reports status to Kubernetes\n30:   - Periodic status updates to AgentRuntime resources\n31:   - Aggregates workspace metrics\n32:   - Updates status subresource with Ready condition\n33:   - Configurable reporting interval (default: 1 minute)\n34:   - Graceful start/stop functionality\n35: \n36: #### 4. `pkg/picod/informer.go`\n37: - **InformerManager**: Manages informer event handlers\n38:   - AgentRuntime informer setup with event handlers\n39:   - CodeInterpreter informer setup with event handlers\n40:   - Spec update detection and handling\n41:   - Deletion detection with graceful shutdown\n42:   - Conditional spec comparison\n43: \n44: ### Modified Files\n45: \n46: #### 1. `pkg/picod/config.go`\n47: - Added `K8sConfig` struct with fields:\n48:   - InCluster: bool\n49:   - KubeconfigPath: string\n50:   - Namespace: string\n51:   - AgentRuntimeName: string\n52:   - AgentRuntimeNamespace: string\n53: - Extended `Config` struct to include optional K8sConfig\n54: \n55: #### 2. `pkg/picod/errors.go`\n56: - Added new error constants:\n57:   - ErrK8sConnectionFailed\n58:   - ErrK8sResourceNotFound\n59:   - ErrK8sUpdateFailed\n60:   - ErrK8sInformerFailed\n61:   - ErrK8sConfigInvalid\n62:   - ErrWorkspaceProvisionFailed\n63:   - ErrWorkspaceCleanupFailed\n64:   - ErrWorkspaceMetricsFailed\n65: - Updated statusCodeMap with appropriate HTTP status codes\n66: \n67: #### 3. `pkg/picod/constants.go`\n68: - Added new environment variables:\n69:   - K8sInClusterEnvVar\n70:   - K8sKubeconfigEnvVar\n71:   - K8sNamespaceEnvVar\n72:   - K8sAgentRuntimeNameEnvVar\n73: - Added new constants:\n74:   - MaxPathLength: 4096 bytes\n75:   - FileLockTimeout: 30 seconds\n76:   - DefaultStatusReportInterval: 1 minute\n77:   - ErrMsgPathTooLong\n78: \n79: #### 4. `pkg/picod/files.go`\n80: - Enhanced `sanitizePath` to be a standalone function accepting workspaceDir parameter\n81: - Maintained backward compatibility with existing Server.sanitizePath method\n82: - Added path length validation\n83: \n84: #### 5. `pkg/picod/server.go`\n85: - Extended Server struct with new fields:\n86:   - k8sClient: *K8sClient\n87:   - workspaceManager: *WorkspaceManager\n88:   - statusReporter: *StatusReporter\n89:   - informerManager: *InformerManager\n90: - Modified NewServer to initialize Kubernetes components when K8sConfig is provided\n91: - Added startup of status reporter goroutine\n92: - Added informer setup and cache synchronization\n93: - Updated Shutdown method to gracefully stop Kubernetes components\n94: - Added getter methods for workspaceManager and k8sClient\n95: \n96: ### Test Files Created\n97: \n98: #### 1. `pkg/picod/k8s_integration_test.go`\n99: - TestK8sConfigValidation: Validates K8sConfig scenarios\n100: - TestK8sClientDefaults: Tests default namespace handling\n101: - TestK8sClientAgentRuntimeName: Tests agent runtime name handling\n102: - TestK8sClientSchemeInitialization: Tests scheme setup\n103: - TestK8sClientStop: Tests graceful shutdown\n104: - TestK8sClientStartInformers: Tests informer startup\n105: - TestK8sClientWaitForCacheSync: Tests cache synchronization\n106: - TestK8sClientInformerSetup: Tests informer setup\n107: \n108: #### 2. `pkg/picod/workspace_manager_test.go`\n109: - Comprehensive tests for workspace lifecycle operations:\n110:   - Provision and cleanup\n111:   - Metrics calculation (empty, with files, with directories)\n112:   - Path resolution and validation\n113:   - File existence, size, mode, modified time\n114:   - Directory operations (create, delete, list)\n115:   - Recursive operations\n116: \n117: #### 3. `pkg/picod/status_reporter_test.go`\n118: - TestNewStatusReporter: Tests reporter creation\n119: - TestNewStatusReporterDefaultInterval: Tests default interval\n120: - TestStatusReporterStop: Tests graceful stop\n121: - TestStatusReporterStartAndStop: Tests start/stop cycle\n122: - TestStatusReporterReportOnce: Tests single status report\n123: \n124: #### 4. `pkg/picod/informer_test.go`\n125: - TestNewInformerManager: Tests manager creation\n126: - TestInformerManagerSetupAgentRuntimeInformer: Tests AgentRuntime informer\n127: - TestInformerManagerSetupCodeInterpreterInformer: Tests CodeInterpreter informer\n128: - TestInformerManagerSpecsEqual: Tests spec comparison\n129: - TestInformerManagerDeepEqual: Tests deep equality checks\n130: \n131: ## Key Features Implemented\n132: \n133: ### 1. Kubernetes Integration\n134: - Dynamic client for CRD operations\n135: - Support for both in-cluster and kubeconfig authentication\n136: - Namespace isolation\n137: - Resource watch and informer capabilities\n138: \n139: ### 2. Workspace Management\n140: - Secure path resolution with workspace jail enforcement\n141: - Workspace lifecycle management (provision, cleanup)\n142: - Metrics tracking (file count, size, directories, last modified)\n143: - File and directory operations\n144: \n145: ### 3. Status Reporting\n146: - Periodic status updates to Kubernetes\n147: - Ready condition management\n148: - Workspace metrics aggregation\n149: - Configurable reporting intervals\n150: \n151: ### 4. Event Handling\n152: - AgentRuntime spec updates\n153: - AgentRuntime deletion with graceful shutdown\n154: - CodeInterpreter spec updates\n155: - CodeInterpreter deletion events\n156: \n157: ### 5. Error Handling\n158: - Comprehensive error types for Kubernetes operations\n159: - Proper HTTP status code mapping\n160: - Graceful degradation when Kubernetes is unavailable\n161: - Detailed error messages without exposing sensitive information\n162: \n163: ### 6. Security\n164: - Workspace jail enforcement prevents directory traversal\n165: - Symlink resolution and validation\n166: - Path length limits\n167: - All operations restricted to workspace boundary\n168: - RBAC-compatible permissions (get, list, watch, update, updatestatus)\n169: \n170: ## Testing\n171: \n172: All tests pass successfully:\n173: - Unit tests for all new components\n174: - Integration tests for Kubernetes client operations\n175: - Workspace operation tests\n176: - Status reporter tests\n177: - Informer management tests\n178: - Error handling tests\n179: \n180: ## Backward Compatibility\n181: \n182: - All existing HTTP APIs remain unchanged\n183: - Kubernetes integration is optional (disabled by default)\n184: - PicoD can run without Kubernetes client (degraded mode)\n185: - No breaking changes to existing deployments\n186: - Existing tests continue to pass\n187: \n188: ## Configuration\n189: \n190: ### CLI Flags (Extended)\n191: - `-k8s-in-cluster`: Use in-cluster Kubernetes config\n192: - `-k8s-kubeconfig`: Path to kubeconfig file\n193: - `-k8s-namespace`: Kubernetes namespace\n194: - `-k8s-agent-runtime`: AgentRuntime resource name\n195: \n196: ### Environment Variables (Extended)\n197: - `PICOD_K8S_IN_CLUSTER`: Set to \"true\" for in-cluster config\n198: - `PICOD_K8S_KUBECONFIG`: Path to kubeconfig file\n199: - `PICOD_K8S_NAMESPACE`: Kubernetes namespace\n200: - `PICOD_K8S_AGENT_RUNTIME_NAME`: AgentRuntime resource name\n201: \n202: ## Documentation\n203: \n204: All code includes:\n205: - Comprehensive comments\n206: - Clear function and type documentation\n207: - Error handling patterns\n208: - Logging for debugging and monitoring\n209: \n210: ## Status\n211: \n212: ✅ **COMPLETE** - All implementation tasks completed successfully\n213: ✅ All files created and modified\n214: ✅ All tests passing\n215: ✅ Code compiles without errors\n216: ✅ Backward compatibility maintained\n217: ✅ Security measures in place\n\n(End of file - total 217 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-016 Implementation Summary\n\n## Overview\nSuccessfully implemented the PicoD file management API with Kubernetes integration, enabling centralized management of PicoD instances and their workspaces through Kubernetes custom resources (AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter).\n\n## Implementation Details\n\n### New Files Created\n\n#### 1. `pkg/picod/k8s_integration.go`\n- **K8sClient**: Manages Kubernetes client operations\n  - Dynamic client for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRDs\n  - Support for in-cluster and kubeconfig-based authentication\n  - Informer factory setup for watch/informer capabilities\n  - Methods for CRUD operations on AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources\n  - Status update support via UpdateStatus\n  - Watch capabilities for real-time resource updates\n\n#### 2. `pkg/picod/workspace_manager.go`\n- **WorkspaceManager**: Manages workspace lifecycle","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-016/IMPLEMENTATION_SUMMARY.md","time":{"start":1775860458064,"end":1775860458096}}}}
